=== TASK ===
# User Profile / My Inquiries

## Overview
Create a secure, premium, and extensible authenticated dashboard for Roam Resort that consolidates the user profile, inquiry history, and account preferences editing. The page must integrate with authentication/authorization (Guests, Hosts, Concierge), an activity timeline with internal notes (staff/hosts visibility as appropriate), session & security management (persistence, active sessions, rate-limiting, audit logging), and provide a guest-facing Inquiry / Transaction History view with statuses (Paid, Pending, Cancelled) and receipts where applicable. All code must be robust against null/undefined values and follow strict runtime safety patterns.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The User Profile / My Inquiries page is the authenticated user dashboard for Roam Resort. It consolidates:
  - Profile details (name, email, contact preferences, verification status)
  - Inquiry history (timeline of inquiries with status, actions, and quick access to details)
  - Account preferences editing (email/password changes, notification preferences, privacy controls)
  - Security & session management (view/terminate active sessions, rate-limiting audit indicators)
  - Notifications/messages from concierge, with status updates
  - For Staff/Hosts: internal notes and lifecycle events exposed to staff roles for relevant inquiries

Goals:
- Provide a cohesive, secure, and elegant dashboard enabling users to review and manage their inquiries, adjust preferences, and verify identity credentials.
- Present a clear lifecycle timeline for inquiries, including email sends and admin actions, with access controls to keep internal notes visible only to staff/hosts where appropriate.
- Ensure session persistence and robust security controls (rate-limiting, audit logging) are observable and controllable by the user for their own sessions.
- For Guests: present Inquiry / Transaction History with statuses (Paid / Pending / Cancelled) and receipts/links when applicable.

Connected features and UI guidance:
- User Authentication & Authorization: Role-based access (Guest, Host, Concierge) with session persistence, email verification, password reset.
- Activity Timeline & Internal Notes: Track events, admin actions, emails; internal notes visible to staff/hosts only as configured.
- Session & Security Management: Show active sessions, allow termination, rate-limit indicators, audit logs.
- Inquiry / Transaction History (Guest): Authenticated guest view listing past inquiries with status and details, plus access to receipts if applicable.

UI elements and visual guidance:
- Profile Summary: avatar placeholder, name, email, phone, language/notification preferences, email verification badge, last login.
- Inquiry History: timeline/list with each inquiry card showing destination, dates, guests, status, amount (if applicable), and action links (View Details, View Receipt).
- Account Actions: Edit profile, Change password, Request account deletion.
- Notifications Panel: Concierge messages and status updates, with filters (All / Unread / Unaddressed).
- Visual emphasis on luxury editorial aesthetic using the provided color palette and typography guidelines.

Visual guidance (as defined in style section) should be applied consistently:
- Colors, typography, spacing, card treatments, hover states, and responsive behavior should reflect Roam Resort’s premium brand.
- Use the specified color palette and typography for all UI components.
- Ensure accessibility considerations (contrast, focus states, keyboard navigability).

---

## Components to Build
- ProfileHeaderCard
  - Displays user avatar, name, email, verification status, and quick actions.
  - Data: user.name, user.email, user.emailVerified, user.contactPrefs, user.phone (optional).
  - Interactions: Edit profile / Change password triggers modals/panels; show verification status badge.

- ProfileEditorPanel
  - Form to update profile fields: name, email, phone, language/locale, notification preferences.
  - Validation: email format, phone format, required fields, password policy hints when editing password.
  - Safety: Debounce changes; submit via API; optimistic UI with error handling.

- InquiriesTimelinePanel
  - List or timeline of inquiries with status, timestamps, and actions.
  - Data: inquiries[], each with id, destination, startDate, endDate, guests, status, amount, receiptUrl, detailsUrl, createdAt.
  - Null-safe access: use (inquiries ?? []) and Array.isArray checks before mapping.
  - Features: filter by status, sort by most recent, click to view details.

- InquiryDetailModal
  - Detailed view for a single inquiry: lifecycle events, emails sent, admin actions, internal notes (staff/hosts only).
  - Data: events[], internalNotes[] (restricted visibility), emails[].
  - Internal notes visibility: render only if user.role is inStaffGroup (e.g., Concierge or Host).

- InternalNotesPanel
  - Editable by staff/hosts for an inquiry, read-only for guests.
  - Data: notes[], author, timestamp, visibility flags.

- SessionManagementPanel
  - List of active sessions for the current user with device, location, last active, and options to terminate.
  - Data: sessions[]. Include rate-limit indicators and audit log snippet.
  - Actions: Terminate session (with confirmation).

- NotificationCenter
  - Panel for concierge messages and status updates related to the user or inquiries.
  - Data: messages[], read/unread status, relatedInquiryId.

- AccountSecurityActions
  - Password reset / two-factor guidance if applicable; re-auth prompts for sensitive actions.

- GuestInquiryHistoryPanel (Connected Page)
  - Authenticated guest view listing past inquiries and their transaction states (Paid / Pending / Cancelled).
  - Data: inquiriesGuest[]. Each item includes id, destination, dates, status, paymentState, receiptUrl, detailsUrl.

- ReceiptLinkCard
  - If receiptUrl is present, display a link/button to view/download receipt.

- API Integration Layer
  - Unified data fetchers for user, inquiries, sessions, notes, and messages with null-safe handling.
  - Centralized error handling and retry policies.

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Framework and structure: React with TypeScript (or the project’s standard). Use functional components with hooks.
- State management: Component-level state with useState/useEffect; lift shared state as needed. If a global store exists (e.g., Redux, Zustand), integrate appropriately.
- Routing: Protected routes ensuring authentication; role-based access guards for Guests, Hosts, Concierge.
- Accessibility: ARIA roles, semantic HTML, keyboard navigation, accessible labels for all inputs and actions.
- Runtime Safety (Mandatory):
  - Supabase-like results: always normalize to arrays using data ?? [].
  - Guard all array operations: (items ?? []).map(...), or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
  - Initialize state for arrays to []: useState<Type[]>([]).
  - Validate API response shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
  - Optional chaining for nested objects: obj?.property?.nested.
  - Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.
- UI Components: Reusable Card, Button, Input, Select, Modal, Tabs, Accordion, Timeline, and Avatar components following the design system.
- Data handling: All API calls should handle 404/500 gracefully; show user-friendly messages. Use loading spinners for network calls.
- Performance: Debounce search/filter in inquiries; paginate inquiry history if large dataset.
- Security: Ensure sensitive actions require re-auth or confirmation; never expose tokens or secrets in frontend.

### Backend
- APIs (REST or GraphQL as per project standards):
  - GET /api/users/me -> fetch current user profile
  - PATCH /api/users/me -> update profile fields
  - POST /api/auth/change-password -> update password
  - GET /api/users/me/sessions -> list active sessions
  - DELETE /api/users/me/sessions/{sessionId} -> terminate session
  - GET /api/users/me/inquiries -> fetch user inquiries with pagination and filters (status, date)
  - GET /api/inquiries/{id} -> fetch detailed inquiry including events, emails, internal notes (notes only for staff/hosts)
  - POST /api/inquiries/{id}/notes -> add internal note (staff/hosts)
  - GET /api/users/me/messages -> notification/concierge messages
  - GET /api/users/me/receipts -> receipts linked to inquiries
  - DTOs should validate shapes and guard against missing fields
- Database tables (conceptual):
  - users: id, name, email, email_verified, phone, locale, preferences
  - sessions: id, user_id, device, ip, last_active, expires_at
  - inquiries: id, user_id, destination_id, start_date, end_date, guests, status, total_amount, payment_state
  - inquiry_events: id, inquiry_id, event_type, timestamp, metadata
  - internal_notes: id, inquiry_id, author_id, content, visible_to (host/concierge)
  - messages: id, user_id, channel, content, read_at, created_at
  - receipts: id, inquiry_id, url, created_at
- Security: enforce role-based access control at API layer; audit logging endpoints for actions (view, update, delete); rate-limiting per user/IP.

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - On page load, fetch current user profile and inquiries; ensure data normalization (data ?? []).
  - When selecting an inquiry, load detail including events and internal notes with access control checks on the client (server must enforce as well).
  - Session panel pulls from /sessions; terminate actions call delete endpoint; reflect changes in UI immediately.
  - Notifications pulled via /messages and shown in NotificationCenter; mark as read on visit or per user action.
- Error handling:
  - Centralized error boundary for UI; map known error codes to user-friendly messages.
  - Ensure all arrays/maps are guarded to avoid null reference errors.

---

## User Experience Flow
- Step 1: User lands on Profile / My Inquiries after authentication.
- Step 2: ProfileHeaderCard displays user details; user can open ProfileEditorPanel to update profile data.
- Step 3: InquiriesTimelinePanel shows a list of inquiries with statuses; user can filter/sort; clicking an inquiry opens InquiryDetailModal.
- Step 4: InquiryDetailModal presents lifecycle events, emails, and a section for internal notes (visible to staff/hosts). Staff can add internal notes via InternalNotesPanel.
- Step 5: SessionManagementPanel shows active sessions; user can terminate any session; receives confirmation.
- Step 6: NotificationCenter shows concierge messages; user can mark as read or act on messages.
- Step 7: AccountSecurityActions allows password change; sensitive actions require re-auth or confirmation.
- Step 8: For Guests: navigate to Guest Inquiry History sub-section (Inquiry / Transaction History) showing past inquiries with status and receipts if applicable; click Receipt to view/download.

---

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models (schema highlights):
  - User: id, name, email, emailVerified, phone, locale, preferences
  - Inquiry: id, userId, destinationId, startDate, endDate, guests, status, totalAmount, paymentState, createdAt
  - InquiryEvent: id, inquiryId, type, timestamp, metadata
  - InternalNote: id, inquiryId, authorId, content, visibleTo (array or enum)
  - Session: id, userId, device, location, ip, lastActive, expiresAt
  - Message: id, userId, channel, content, readAt, createdAt
  - Receipt: id, inquiryId, url, createdAt
- API Endpoints (examples):
  - GET /api/users/me
  - PATCH /api/users/me
  - GET /api/users/me/inquiries
  - GET /api/inquiries/{id}
  - POST /api/inquiries/{id}/notes
  - GET /api/users/me/sessions
  - DELETE /api/users/me/sessions/{id}
  - GET /api/users/me/messages
  - GET /api/users/me/receipts
- Security:
  - JWT or session-based auth with refresh tokens
  - Role-based access control checks on every API
  - Audit logging for critical actions (profile updates, note additions, session termination, status changes)
- Validation:
  - Use robust input validation on both client and server
  - Ensure optional fields are handled gracefully
  - Validate date formats, currency amounts, and required fields
- Validation rules examples:
  - Email must be valid format
  - Password must meet policy (min length, complexity) for updates
  - Dates must be valid and startDate <= endDate
  - Status must be one of: New, Contacted, Deposit Paid, Confirmed, Cancelled

